    "The same subsets are used across methods, ensuring differences arise from the merging algorithms rather than checkpoint selection.",
    "Benchmarks.",
    "We evaluate every base model and merged configuration with the lm-evaluation-harness library (Biderman et al., 2024), using its standardized implementations for the following Open LLM Leaderboard tasks: arc_easy, arc_challenge, hellaswag, winogrande, boolq, piqa, openbookqa, commonsense_qa, headqa, prost, truthfulqa_mc1, mmlu, medmcqa, leaderboard_gpqa, leaderboard_bbh, and leaderboard_mmlu_pro.",
    "These benchmarks collectively cover multiple evaluation axes including commonsense and scientific question answering (e.g., commonsense_qa, medmcqa), multi-step reasoning (e.g., arc_challenge, bbh), and instruction-following (e.g., hellaswag, winogrande).",
    "In Fig. 3, we show the average performance across benchmarks for all merged models and merging methods (task-wise accuracies are in Section B)."
